# Appendix E: Linear Recombination & Error Bounds (Proposition 6.1)

**Proposition 6.1 (Cartesian Recombination).** *Let $z_{\text{new}} = \alpha \Pi_{G_1}(z) + \beta \Pi_{G_2}(z)$. If $\mathcal{P}_{G_1} F \mathcal{P}_{G_2} \approx 0$, then the output error satisfies:*
$$\| f_\theta(z_{\text{new}}) - \alpha f_{G_1}(z) - \beta f_{G_2}(z) \| \leq \mathcal{O}(\| \Pi_{G_1} z \|^2 \| \Pi_{G_2} z \|^2).$$

**Proof.** Expand $f_\theta$ via Taylor series around the origin in the linear representation layer (residual stream):
$$f_\theta(z_{\text{new}}) = f_\theta(0) + J_\theta z_{\text{new}} + \frac{1}{2} z_{\text{new}}^\top H_f z_{\text{new}} + \mathcal{O}(\|z_{\text{new}}\|^3),$$
where $J_\theta$ is the Jacobian. Substituting $z_{\text{new}} = \alpha \Pi_{G_1}z + \beta \Pi_{G_2}z$:
$$J_\theta z_{\text{new}} = \alpha J_\theta \Pi_{G_1}z + \beta J_\theta \Pi_{G_2}z = \alpha f_{G_1}(z) + \beta f_{G_2}(z) - f_\theta(0).$$
The quadratic term contains cross-products $\Pi_{G_1}z \, H_f \, \Pi_{G_2}z$. By the decoupling assumption, $H_f$ (proportional to $F(\theta)$ in the output layer) is block-diagonal across $G_1, G_2$, so cross-terms vanish: $\Pi_{G_1} H_f \Pi_{G_2} \approx 0$. Thus:
$$f_\theta(z_{\text{new}}) = \alpha f_{G_1}(z) + \beta f_{G_2}(z) + \mathcal{O}(\| \Pi_{G_1} z \|^2 \| \Pi_{G_2} z \|^2).$$
The error is second-order in subspace energies, confirming that recombination is exact in the linear regime and incurs negligible distortion under block-diagonal dominance. $\square$

