# Appendix G: Notation & Regularity Assumptions

### G.1 Notation
| Symbol | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| $\mathcal{X}, \mathcal{Y}$ | Input/output spaces |
| $f_\theta: \mathcal{X} \to \mathcal{Y}$ | Parametric model |
| $\theta \in \mathbb{R}^D$ | Parameter vector, $D \sim 10^{13}$ |
| $P_{\text{data}}, P_{\text{web}}$ | Training and full web distributions |
| $F(\theta)$ | Fisher Information Matrix |
| $H(\theta)$ | Hessian $\nabla_\theta^2 \mathcal{L}(\theta)$ |
| $\mathcal{P}_{\mathcal{M}_i}$ | Orthogonal projector onto FIM eigenspace for concept $i$ |
| $\mathcal{M}_G$ | Low-dimensional manifold encoding grammar $G$ |
| $\mathcal{L}_{\text{eff}}$ | SGD effective loss with trace regularization |
| $\delta$ | Marginal predictive utility threshold |
| $\text{eff}(P)$ | Participation ratio: $(\sum \lambda_k)^2 / \sum \lambda_k^2$ |

### G.2 Regularity Assumptions
1. **Smoothness:** $\mathcal{L}(\theta)$ is $L$-smooth and $\mu$-convex in local neighborhoods of minima.
2. **Bounded Gradients:** $\|\nabla \mathcal{L}(\theta)\| \leq G_{\max}$ almost everywhere.
3. **Gradient Noise:** $\mathbb{E}[\xi_t | \theta_t] = 0$, $\text{Cov}(\xi_t | \theta_t) \approx \frac{\eta}{B} H(\theta_t)$.
4. **Decoupling Stability:** $\|\mathcal{P}_{\mathcal{M}_i} F(\theta) \mathcal{P}_{\mathcal{M}_j}\|_F \leq \epsilon_D$ with $\epsilon_D \to 0$ as $D \to \infty$.
5. **Utility Positivity:** $\delta > \lambda \|\theta^*\|^2$ ensures subspace persistence against weight decay.

These assumptions are standard in modern deep learning theory and align with empirical observations in overparameterized transformers.


